title: Brain abscess, cyst or encephalitis and driving

heading_context: Brain abscess, cyst or encephalitis and driving
chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you have a brain abscess, cyst or encephalitis.
chunks.plain_content:
Brain abscess, cyst or encephalitis and driving
You must tell DVLA if you have a brain abscess, cyst or encephalitis.

heading_context: Brain abscess, cyst or encephalitis and driving
chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. If you’re involved in an accident, you may be prosecuted.
chunks.plain_content:
Brain abscess, cyst or encephalitis and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. If you’re involved in an accident, you may be prosecuted.

heading_context: Brain abscess, cyst or encephalitis and driving
chunks.html_content: Fill in form B1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
